metadata.name: Hatch Field 001 #191
metadata.description:
Genesis p5js drawing on fx(hash). Experimenting with translating recent work in done in Grasshopper exploring hatch patterns to p5.js. By Andrew Kudless / Matsys @matsysdesign
There are four feature groups:
- Base Hue: Red, Orange, Yellow, Spring Green, Green, Ocean Green, Cyan, Sky Blue, Blue, Purple, Magenta, and Crimson. Each has the same random chance of being the base color (12%).
- Hue Range: Narrow (14%), Wide (51%), and Infinite(34%)
- Lineweight: Thin (75%), Medium (10%), Thick (10%), Extra Thick (5%)
-Fray: Loose (90%), Tight (10%)

metadata.name: A Slight Case of Overbombing #16
metadata.description:
Inspired by monochromatic art of the late 60s, Russian folk-art woodblock prints, and the stylised colours of British underground comics, excited to introduce a series of bold rich landscapes. England, Wales, Ireland and Scotland represented by red, yellow, green and blue, sometimes a house or two, and groovy clouds.

Instructions ::

.     - speed up
,     - slow down
space - pause
n     - toggle noise
p     - cycle palette
h     - toggle high-res (and definitely intentional pixel shift)
s     - download and save image

metadata.name: ProcGen Entomology #483
metadata.description:
Realtime 3D in-browser procedural generation of insect-like models, with a look reminiscent of vintage entomology illustrations.

The project is about the fact that insects are cool first and foremost.
This is also about nostalgia.

Everything is procedural except for the font. The exposed features only describe the most visible parts.

I wrote mord words, about where it came from, and some technical details on the procedural aspect at:
https://ulucode.com/projects/entomology/

GPU Required!

Interface : 
Space : show/hide menu
Mouse Left : Rotate
Mouse Right : Pan
Mouse Middle/Wheel : Zoom

Captures only work in Live mode.

metadata.name: string_pllu #82
metadata.description:
Making some abstract plants, inspired by a painting technique called string pull.

Connect some random semi circles with strings and pull the strings from the bottom of the canvas.

The semi circles rotate while moving to create some random brush strokes.

metadata.name: Phaces #58
metadata.description:
Faces + Phases = Phaces. A living artwork celebrating variety and community, with a healthy dose of delayed gratification.

Each Phace starts in black and white, a simple but fascinating look at the variety that can emerge from a few lines of code. It is a sober start to an exciting journey and a reminder that good things take time.

Each week, your Phace evolves. You‚Äôll see the next evolution every Saturday for 12 weeks, providing moments for the collector community to come together to share and celebrate the latest Phaces ‚Äì there will be some wild ones in there!

Each Phace has a name, generated from a list of 144 adjectives and a 144 names randomly selected from the US census. Other features hint at the exciting evolutions to come. You know that Nonchalant Erma with Palette = Electric and Colour Boost = Wild is going to be up for a party. 

We won‚Äôt say much more, for risk of spoiling the surprises but we can‚Äôt wait to see your Phaces emerge and evolve over these coming weeks. Follow along for updates on Twitter, Insta and at https://www.phaust.art/.

------

Edition Size: 156. A tribute to the inspiration and evolution of fxHash over the 156 day beta. 

Palettes: Azure, Bioluminant, Day Glo, Electric, Lava Lamp, Livid, Peach, Peacock, Powder, Retro, Royal, Turple.

Evolutions: 12.

S: to save current Phace. All saves are at high resolution.
G: to save a grid of all revealed Phaces.
1-9, 0, E, T: to save a specific Phace ‚Äì one to nine, then ten, eleven and twelve.

metadata.name: Spher #1
metadata.description:
Spher are 3D interactive sculptures resulting from the exploration of line drawings with vertex shaders and spherical coordinates. A sculpture is formed by many lines being drawn simultaneously while folding and unfolding following patterns on the surface of a sphere.

For a full experience read the instructions and export a high resolution image of your favorite perspectives.


Instructions:

- use the mouse to navigate (zoom, pan and drag)
- press 'c' to switch between multiple camera angles
- press 'b' to pause the animation
- press 'p' to download the current view it in a custom resolution

Made with threejs and custom shaders by @bgola
Berlin, April 2022

metadata.name: The Weight of Winter #25
metadata.description:
Description of Seasons of Siskiyou Series

Surrounding my home, covering more than one million acres, is the Rogue River - Siskiyou National Forest which takes up three southern Oregon counties and one northern California county.  It‚Äôs a magical place that fills the imagination and lifts the spirit; a place that inspires with its uniqueness, its legends, and its larger-than-life vistas.

Each season in the Siskiyous is a unique experience unto itself.  So, with an attention to the feelings this place evokes at any given time of the year, I designed four generative tokens to create an impression of the emotion‚Äìthe calming quietness; the peaceful solitude; the overwhelming contrasts and variety of forms, shapes and textures; the magic and playful mystery; the welcomingness and foreboding.  These four works feature clever and inventive creative coding techniques in a rich, graphic style to craft a stunning impression of the Seasons of Siskiyou.


Token 4 of 4 - The Weight of Winter (1990 x 1080) p5js Generative Token.

All good things must come to an end.  After a glorious time of renewal and rebirth, the months of growth and bounty come to a close.  A time of reflection and rest approaches.  All that can be done has been done; and, all one can do is endure the season of slumber.

As light fades with the shyness of the sun, the need to sleep takes over as the creatures of the wilderness test their preparedness.  Travelers to warner lands have offered farewell to those brave enough to stand against the coming snows.  Those who have remained will carry the weight of winter.  The festival of fall had provided so much to carry them through to the colors of spring.  Has it been enough?

The weight of winter can be crushing; but, it‚Äôs the pressure that shapes the designs of persistence, endurance and perseverance required to fight against it.  With its paler of indifference, the monochrome landscape of winter hides the brilliance of those schemes aimed at mastering the challenges of survival.  With their perfect adaptations, nature survives to take on winter‚Äôs heft with defiant joyfulness and triumphant serenity.  

The Weight of Winter features a generative atmosphere with distant mountains; flow-field conifer trees on noise-wave foothills; a random cluster of subject conifers in the mid-space; and a flow-field tree branch with an interpolated dusting of snow.  Diamond dust ‚Äì small spears of ice ‚Äì are simulated with an optical-effect along with random snowflakes.  A generative ‚Äòconspiracy‚Äô of ravens are scattered along the tree tops.

Once the scene is completely generated, a framing box will appear.  Press the DOWN ARROW to save the scene as a png image file.  Click or tap the canvas to toggle full screen mode.

Token Published May 9, 2022 on FXHASH set at 75 Editions.
Written and designed by Ed Cavett using the p5js library.
Token 4 of 4 from the series ‚ÄúThe Seasons of Siskiyou.‚Äù

metadata.name: The Face We Had #193
metadata.description:
The Face We Had is a series of generative, moving sculptures attempting to express the artists personal thoughts, experiences and inclinations related to meditative and altered states of consciousness. In a non-descriptive way, the piece aims to reflect the always changing nature of mind through patterns of movement and assemblages of form, color and organic shapes, endlessly revolving around a perceived point of origin.  

Although not intended as literal depictions, the elements interact in a way that could be interpreted as dance-like interactions between thought patterns, mental energy, feelings, fragments of memories and layers of personal identity. 



Interactive features:

space - pause/play
w - wireframe view
d - debug view (compute textures)
s - save screenshot
